Nutrition of children suffering from obesity: No breakfast and sausage for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 are overweight; while 9% of schoolchildren are overweight, 5% are obese.
According to the latest study, children suffering from obesity usually come from families that lead an unhealthy lifestyle.
Once again, we see the importance of the environment and behavioral patterns accompanying a person for his or her healthy development.
For example, sausage appears on the tables of children suffering from obesity, almost twice as often as in families with children with normal weight.
More than 19% of obese children ate French fries for dinner on the eve of a survey related to an educational event called Obesity is no accident.
Moreover, families of children suffering from obesity do not play sports. This, however, applies to the majority of families of modern schoolchildren - only 15% of children said that their parents find time to play sports at least once a week.
The study was conducted among 900 children.
The study was conducted at the end of the last academic year and involved nearly 900 elementary school students across Bohemia.
The Obesity event was held for the second year in a row, with the support of the insurance company Obesná zdravní poji<0xC5><0xA1>t'ovna and Unilever.
To date, more than 12,000 pupils from grades 4 to 8 have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and sufficient athletic activity are the main determinants of the rapidly growing number of children who suffer from either overweight or obesity.
“For example, only half of the respondents said they eat five times a day, according to the breakfast-meal-meal-meal-meal-meal-meal-meal scheme, and this is one of the prerequisites for proper nutrition,” says one of the findings of the study.
No lunch or sausages in the evenings.
Experts warn that for healthy development, even such relative details as the constant time of the family breakfast are important.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren’s families have breakfast together.
Most families eat breakfast separately.
The worst finding was that in every tenth family, people don’t eat breakfast at all.
And yet breakfast is the basis of the correct daily diet.
The study found that fried foods are more commonly consumed in families with children suffering from obesity.
Almost everyone – regardless of weight – drinks sugary soft drinks every day (70%).
Although more than 40% of children exercise regularly, this figure is more than halved – up to 15% – when it comes to their parents.
Make your own menu.
In another part of the study, selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) were asked to make their own menu based on the products offered and based on their tastes and preferences.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged 12-15 are far from ideal when it comes to healthy eating."
Their favorite food includes a large number of flour, meat and sweet dishes.
“The high popularity of sweetened beverages is of particular concern,” the study concludes.
As the main dinner dish, the pasta defeated the bird with a small margin.
However, the children showed little interest in legumes, fish and vegetable dishes.
Striving for a healthy lifestyle
The study also found that children are willing to change their eating habits provided they are provided with relevant information.
"Many participants in the control group of the study showed a significant shift in preferences towards healthy food when filling out the questionnaire after the lecture Obesity is not an accident," the results of the project say.
This was especially noticeable, for example, in the case of sugary soft drinks - more children began to prefer them just water.
In addition, as a main dish, children were more likely to mark the poultry and fish, limiting the number of sweet dishes and pastries.
A stylist should also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the first article on training for stylists, I complained about the amount of information in the introductory classes.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three experts in the field; tips on choosing clothes for non-standard figures; and a seminar on how it all works in real life.
Further - more.
The closer we get to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
The training takes place every Saturday and Sunday, but it is really full of information.
This time with Alenka, the director, (there is not a single man in the course) we discussed how to dress a woman whose body is not perfectly symmetrical.
Most women are not completely symmetrical.
One has a short neck, the other has a boyish figure without proper shapes, another weighs more than normal.
The stylist should know how to visually reduce broad shoulders, lengthen the neck or add missing volumes.
We were given advice on how to emphasize the figure of women like Jennifer Lopez, i.e. the owners of more lush breasts and thighs and narrow waist, without wearing them too provocative.
For example, if the difference in the volume of the waist and hips is so great that you can not pick up a skirt or trousers, it is worth having at least one thing sewn to order.
You will clearly not regret the invested funds, since ideally sitting clothes are invaluable.
In a skirt made to order, you will feel much better than in one that constantly moves away, rolls down, strips the waist, etc.
Owners of boyish figures, on the other hand, can wear clothes with ruffles, appliques, embroidery or folds.
Given the abundance of this kind of information and the types of figures, I’m glad I have a whole week to realize it all.
And yet, I'm afraid that's too much, given the homework we've been given.
Each participant of the course had to come up with two outfits for any celebrity: for the day and for the evening.
We must take into account their modern appearance, their style in clothes and the type of figure.
I’m going to dress up Miranda Kerr, who you may know from Victoria’s Secret advertising campaigns.
I’m happy for myself because it’s a lot easier to wear than, say, Britney Spears, Christine Aguilera, who recently gained a ton (please keep in mind that I’m exaggerating), or the very young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut clothes out of magazines or find them on the Internet, print and process them using graphics programs.
Mudboard – so called the result of the work – then reflects our own style and attitude to the graphic image.
It is important to keep in mind the graphical component of the style.
The stylist does not just dress real people, but creates grocery pages in magazines (based on special instructions, for example, fashion bags, coats, etc.).
This is what stylist and designer Mario Kamenik told us.
But that was only on Sunday.
A stylist needs general knowledge
The Saturday lecture, full of information about the types of figures, was revived by three guests - specialists in this field.
Stylist, Honza Pokorny; fashion designer, Jakub Polanka; and fashion photographer Ben Ranch.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and the stylist should use this fact.
A good stylist knows how to use one item of clothing in different ways.
In this case, diversity is the key to success.
For example, a trench coat can be worn the usual way, on top of jeans and t-shirts, like a coat; but it can also be worn on the naked body, without clasps, like a dress.
Another option is to roll up the sleeves or lift the collar, and the whole image changes completely.
“Play with him,” he said.
Anyway, I appreciated the following advice the most: "For your work, you need to know the rules perfectly."
Then you can start breaking them," Jacob told us.
Here I finally understood why we are studying all the definitions and rules, what to combine with what and why, while in fashion magazines we often see completely different.
Not to mention fashion shows.
I learned from Ben, a photographer, that a stylist should have more outfit options on hand than the number of photos he needs to take.
So, for a ten-page fashion review (equivalent to ten outfits) I must be prepared to create at least fifteen images.
Now I also know that in the picture the item of clothing often looks and works in combination with others in a completely different way than in reality.
We have to keep that in mind when we create an image.
Honza Pokorny confirmed that often the image and style is half the success.
Just take a look at Madonna, who doesn’t have a striking vocal, but her image and marketing have made her a global star.
The attitude towards the services of stylists in the Czech Republic is still quite cool.
Even famous people often find it superfluous (and believe that it is enough to be an expert in something, and the way they look - secondary).
And if someone finally lets us create their style, we should expect them to name us a different (lesser) size than the one they actually wear.
Then we turn to Google and find out if the tabloids have written anything about some celebrity getting fat/skinny, etc.
On Sunday, Honza and Mario emphasized that it is not enough for a stylist to understand fashion and be able to pick up a outfit.
Our work mainly consists of communicating with the people we dress; therefore, it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to judge people, not to condone them and stick to their opinion.
“If a manager asks you to look at her clothes and add a few beautiful things, you can’t throw away her entire wardrobe by telling her that her clothes are awful.”
“Find at least a few things you can praise and advise what you can wear with them,” says Mario.
He also showed us what exactly should fit a work bag.
This is a bag that you tie around your waist to carry everything you need.
In addition to the obvious things such as scissors, sticky roller or English pins, it should have a nylon thread (stylists use it when shooting some items, such as bags or hats), special clips to fasten the fabric on the back in case the clothes are too large (blows and similar items are prohibited for clothes) or set because they spoil the clothes)
In order to distract from the lectures and gain some practical experience, we learned how to properly make the linings on the soles of shoes.
Even when shooting in a studio where the floor is smooth, the soles can get damaged – not to mention shooting outdoors.
And here we go with the glue.
You should not touch the shoes with scissors, so as not to spoil them.
It requires real skill.
I was pleased that Mario praised my work.
I did not like the skills mentioned.
This is only part of what we heard during the second part of the weekend course.
I’m starting to realize that being a professional stylist isn’t that easy, no matter what you say.
V Need for Speed: Escape takes place in America.
Revision
What was supposed to be a carefree walk turned into a routine morning commute to work due to a series of completely inappropriate and careless mistakes.
The ambitions were satisfied to some extent, but that didn’t matter, because no one clearly wanted to do the extra work.
Before the release of the new version with the subtitle "Escape" was associated with high hopes.
It was expected to move the previous Need For Speed series in a new direction; demo versions indicated that the game would take a worthy place in the genre of racing games.
We were curious to see the parts of the game where the main character gets out of the car and runs.
As is often the case with NFS, it ends up being a lot different than we expected.
The game is quite a good arcade race, but the overall impression spoils several unnecessary mistakes that are present in this series of games for several years.
So, in fact, these are not errors, but a manifestation of the inexplicable laziness of the developers.
The adventure begins very well.
You become part of a story whose main character, Jack, decides to solve some personal problems by participating in an illegal race through America.
You get in a car on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your task is to get to New York first.
This idea has some interesting features.
The route consists of ten stages, divided into more than fifty races.
This means that each race takes place on its own route, individual stages are held in a diverse and interesting environment.
Therefore, there is no feeling that the same thing is happening all the time in the game.
Despite the fact that the graphics are at the same level as in the previous parts of the series, some tracks are nice to look at.
And yet the game does not cause strong emotions.
Although driving through the desert, in the autumn suburbs or high in the snowy mountains is very pleasant.
In addition, the race from time to time brings to life an unusual detail.
For example, in the desert, you fall into a sandstorm that significantly reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains you need to be careful not to fall under the avalanche.
The races are pretty well organized.
There are only a few varieties, but that’s enough.
For a while you are trying to overtake several opponents (essentially a normal race); then you are trying to improve time (a standard race with a stopwatch); or you are competing against one opponent.
Among other things, from time to time you run into the police, which makes your task even more difficult.
The components on the outside of the car are new.
This is just an interactive animation where most of the time Jack runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right time.
It's not complicated.
Although surprisingly, these fragments are much smaller than you might expect (only three to be exact).
In fact, it turns out that this is good for the game because this property is not boring; given all of the above, this is one of the things that make the game more entertaining.
The racing model follows in the footsteps of previous models.
This means that it is no longer something special, but it cannot be considered a disadvantage.
If you’re looking for an imitation of real life, you’ll have to look elsewhere.
And yet, this driving model is very suitable for dynamic racing, although there are better options on the market.
So far, so good.
After a while, however, the problems begin.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is not so good.
You don’t expect complicated transformations and collisions from such a game, but if you have no idea before a collision with an object how your car will behave, something is wrong.
Usually, overtaking or driving past cars in a dense stream, you sometimes slightly touch another car. And yet sometimes in almost a similar situation, your car begins to spin wildly.
Or smashed up.
It’s not that important thanks to the restart system, but it’s enough to ruin the fun.
The restarts are arranged so that if you crash or go far away from the track, the game takes you back to the point where it stopped.
However, there are only five reboots available for each race.
If you use them all, you will have to start the race from the beginning.
This is useful in case something doesn’t work out, but you can’t fully rely on it.
Sometimes reboots are not enough, and you have to memorize a separate section of the race.
An important drawback of the game is the fact that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some turns need to be done in a certain way, otherwise you just won’t fit in.
In other cases, you meet civilian cars in a certain place in the same configuration regardless of whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see your opponent easily drive between two cars moving in the opposite direction, whereas when you find yourself there, the cars are already arranged in such a way that you need to either bypass them or reduce speed.
It doesn’t matter when you’re next to them; everything is arranged so that the situation always happens right in front of your nose.
Competitors have other advantages.
During the game, you discover several places where, no matter the time, the same opponent overtakes you in the same place.
This is especially evident at the end of the game, on a long bridge where you drive in the opposite direction.
Obviously, your opponent must stand in front of you no matter what.
The fact is that when it rides in front of you, it worsens your visibility, leading to one or more accidents at that site.
You can understand the attempt to make the game more interesting and filled with adrenaline, but it is so obvious that it quickly begins to cause irritation.
It’s a pity, because despite the simple driving model, the game is entertaining and sometimes so eventful that you don’t have time to pay attention to what’s happening around you.
It doesn’t matter what keeps you bored – a concept with fifty unique tracks, a sequence of races or something else.
The idea of changing cars during races is unusual.
You need to keep track of the gas stations along the way, as it is on them that your car can change, despite the fact that in most cases the one you already have is quite enough.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for cities; powerful American cars for straight sections of the highway; and exotic super sports cars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain tracks.
The main mode of story mode is closely related to the mode of challenge mode; these are races on individual sections, which you will learn during the game.
Here you win for your personal business both medals and points common to the challenges and story modes.
Many possibilities are available for obtaining a higher level of driving: from cars to profile data.
In addition, the profile is linked to the online Autolog feature, which, among other things, compares your results with those of other players and provides public communication.
Here’s another flaw that’s hard to understand; it’s an example from the last race in the sequence.
You and your car get into a subway tunnel (let’s assume it is), where you race on the rails in the dark (let’s assume it is).
Your speedometer shows figures from 150 to 200 km/h (assuming so), when a subway train suddenly crashes at your back, turning your car into a pile of scrap metal.
For several days, our editorial staff discussed whether no one really thought for a second at the time of creating the game, or whether its creators really think we are such idiots.
The technical component of the game is nothing special; but the overall impression of the video series is mostly pleasant, sometimes even stunning.
Although it is a pity that in some critical moments the quality of the recording, sometimes quite severely, decreases.
This is especially true for incidents with a large number of participants, where a good record wouldn’t help you much either.
The sound is fine; the soundtrack is for the amateur.
In order to please the widest possible youth audience, the soundtrack 'included songs from different styles'; but it is unlikely that many people will buy the game because of its music.
Need for Speed: Escape is pretty messy.
If the game had avoided clearly unnecessary mistakes, we could honestly say Escape is the best part of NFS for the last few years.
In any case, the game leaves a feeling of incompleteness.
Of course, this is a good pastime, but be prepared for the fact that the shortcomings will blind you as the airport spotlight.
