There are so many of them that I can talk all day about the bassists I love.
How did Pearl Jam succeed in keeping grunge relevant, even though it is no longer in vogue?
I think we all feel a certain detachment from the word grunge.
When I think about it, it reminds me of bands I’ve mentioned before, like Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all that came out at the same time, and if it matters now, I think it’s wonderful because it’s music that’s worth listening to, and bands like Mudhoney are making music better than ever.
At first, your music was darker, but now it’s more positive.
How do you explain this change?
It’s interesting because I think there are a few songs on the album that may seem easier, but there are songs like The End or Just Breathe that are considered very gloomy, although they may sound a little bit positive.
