Fujimori was hospitalized again for medical examination
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized on Tuesday at a state hospital for examination for muscle loss seen in his legs, his family doctor said.
Fujimori, 72, who was sentenced to 25 years in prison for human rights abuses committed during his reign (1990-2000), suffers from several diseases, including tongue cancer, which has left him under observation and surgery four times.
