According to statistics released Monday by the FBI, anti-Muslim crimes increased by almost 50% between 2009 and 2010, while other forms of racial and religious violence declined slightly or remained unchanged over the same period.
According to these figures, the total number of cases of violence against Muslims increased from 107 in 2009 to 160 in 2010, an increase of 49%, compared to a 13% increase in cases of violence against Catholics, a 4% decrease in attacks against Jews and a 14% increase in the total number of religious crimes.
